<br>
What's in it?  First, input your level, select your instruments from the drop-down boxes and it will show you the actual song effects.  It's also got information on stacking and overwriting (both other songs and spells), where the songs can be found or drop, a quick reference for what level we get various skills and disciplines, and info about instrument effects.  Learn the data in this puppy and you'll be a LOT more effective.<br>
<br>
BTW, no one has mentioned instruments.  For percussion, Walrus Skin Drums give you excellent bang for your buck (30% bonus to percussion songs, third best in the game) - saw some in the bazaar recently for under 1K.  As an alternative, you can buy the Ancient Coins from Kunark for the Nostrolo's Tamborine quest (see EQ Diva for details on that).  Much more tedious but it's not a bad instrument.  If you see a deal on Selo's Drums of the March (from Naggy) go for those - last seen selling for 20K.  (You can have mine when you pry it from my cold dead fingers.)<br>
<br>
For strings - if you can find a Lute of the Howler for under 10K, or if you have additional money to burn, snag it.  You can't use the WW illusion until 40th, but it's a one-handed instrument and you can dual wield with it at 17th.  Otherwise, just buy the Combine string instrument in Katta - at least as good as the gypsy lute from MM.<br>
<br>
It's not often you'll need to equip winds or brass except for skill-ups, so don't shell out a ton for either of those.<br>
<br>
For RL, go buy a bunch of ice packs or ziplock baggies for ice for your wrists.  You'll need'em. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
TTFN,<br>
